.
|-- wordcount.cc               # wordcount example source code
|-- Makefile                   # makefile for wordcount.cc
|-- Makefile.rules             # enviroment setting for makefile
|-- mrl-wordcount              # compiled binary for suse 64bit platform
|
|                              # shell scripts for testing Mapreduce-Lite
|-- wordcount_run_locally.sh   
|-- wordcount_batch_reduction_mode.sh
|-- wordcount_incremental_reduction_mode.sh
|
|-- testdata                   # testdata for wordcount job
    |-- text-00000-of-00002
    `-- text-00001-of-00002


#------------------------------
# Mapreduce-Lite Quick Start
#------------------------------

1. Read "wordcount_run_locally.sh", this script is used to test Mapreduce-Lite
in local machine, modify the local IP address if necessary, and run the script.

2. Read "wordcount_incremental_reduction_mode.sh", this script is used to test
INCREMENTAL reduction mode of Mapreduce-Lite in multiple machines, modify IP
addresses if necessary. Make sure the testdatas are well prepared in the
specified directory in all machines, then run the script.

3. Read and run "wordcount_batch_reduction_mode.sh", this script is used to
test BATCH reduction mode of Mapreduce-Lite in multiple machines
